<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="87" pageId="6" pageNumber="86" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,335,1320,1346]" box="[189,335,1320,1346]" pageId="6" pageNumber="86">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,335,1320,1346]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="6" pageNumber="86" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,335,1320,1346]" pageId="6" pageNumber="86">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,934,1367,1429]" box="[234,298,1367,1393]" pageId="6" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,298,1367,1393]" pageId="6" pageNumber="86">Male</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,934,1367,1429]" box="[189,934,1402,1429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="86">
MEASUREMENTS. Total length (forewing apices curved): 
<quantity box="[837,930,1402,1429]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="6" pageNumber="86" unit="mm" value="2.8">2.8 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[188,1399,1468,1846]" pageId="6" pageNumber="86">
STRUCTURE. Metope slightly depressed below upper margin, with very weak and short median carina and weak sublateral carinae running from upper margin to slightly beyond eyes, but not reaching metopoclypeal suture (
<figureCitation box="[459,556,1538,1564]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[239,1345,966,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-176@7.[224,1364,956,1924]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Superciliaris tawaiensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH), external view. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Frontal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761690" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761690/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="86">Figs 3C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[570,605,1538,1564]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[308,1258,279,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-12@8.[308,1279,265,1783]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Superciliaris spp., external view (weak carinae and margins are indicated by dotted lines). A–C. S. anichkini sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ZIN). A. Half of face and left paranotal lobe, frontal view. B. Face, frontal view. C. Tegula and basal part of forewing, lateral view. D–E. S. celebensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH). D. Face, frontal view. E. Tegula and basal part of forewing, lateral view. F–G. S. tawaiensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH). F. Face, frontal view. G. Tegula and basal part of forewing, lateral view. Abbreviation: sc = sublateral carinae of metope. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761692" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761692/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="86">4F</figureCitation>
). Metope and coryphe joined at nearly right angle (in lateral view) (
<figureCitation box="[199,292,1573,1600]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[239,1345,966,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-176@7.[224,1364,956,1924]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Superciliaris tawaiensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH), external view. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Frontal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761690" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761690/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="86">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
). Coryphe transverse, nearly 2.5× as wide as long at midline; anterior margin nearly straight; posterior margin concave (
<figureCitation box="[504,597,1609,1635]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[239,1345,966,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-176@7.[224,1364,956,1924]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Superciliaris tawaiensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH), external view. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Frontal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761690" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761690/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="86">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Coryphe longitudinally striated medially, with pair of weak bulges laterally. Postclypeus with smooth median carina. Pronotum 0.5 × as long as coryphe at midline, without bulges or carinae. Mesonotum 4 × as long as pronotum, with fine median carina and pair of lateral bulges. Forewings without bulges. Hind tibia with two lateral spines above middle and with five apical spines. First metatarsomere slightly longer than second one, but distinctly wider, with long setae ventrally and with two latero-apical and five intermediate spines. Second metatarsomere with two latero-apical spines only.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1401,1885,1982]" lastBlockId="7.[189,1398,265,326]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="87" pageId="6" pageNumber="86">
COLORATION (
<figureCitation box="[346,420,1885,1911]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[239,1345,966,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-176@7.[224,1364,956,1924]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Superciliaris tawaiensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH), external view. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Frontal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761690" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761690/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="86">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). General coloration dark brown, with black punctuation. Eyes light. 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1276,1290,1885,1899]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="86">rd</superScript>
segment of rostrum light brown outside and dark brown behind. Forewings with light yellow spots in cells of apical part of clavus and ventro-apical half of corium. Forewing appendix (hardly visible on left wing on 
<figureCitation box="[227,320,265,291]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[239,1345,966,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-176@7.[224,1364,956,1924]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Superciliaris tawaiensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH), external view. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Frontal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761690" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761690/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="87">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
) light brown yellowish from apex of clavus to dorso-lateral angle. Hind femora and tibiae brown. Apices of leg spines black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[188,1400,366,673]" pageId="7" pageNumber="87">
MALE TERMINALIA (
<figureCitation box="[416,492,366,392]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[187,230,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[259,1323,598,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-121@11.[212,1376,554,1890]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 7. Superciliaris tawaiensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH), genitalia. A. Penis, lateral view.B. Penis, ventral view. C. Anal tube, dorsal view. D. Anal tube, lateral view. E. Style, lateral view. F. Style, dorsal view. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761698" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761698/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="87">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Pygofer vertically elongate, with convex hind margins. Anal tube nearly twice as long as wide medially, distinctly enlarged from base to apex (in dorsal view) (
<figureCitation box="[1227,1321,401,427]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[187,230,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[259,1323,598,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-121@11.[212,1376,554,1890]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 7. Superciliaris tawaiensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH), genitalia. A. Penis, lateral view.B. Penis, ventral view. C. Anal tube, dorsal view. D. Anal tube, lateral view. E. Style, lateral view. F. Style, dorsal view. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761698" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761698/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="87">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
). Anal column long and narrow, not surpassing posterior margin of anal tube (
<figureCitation box="[1009,1138,436,462]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[187,230,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[259,1323,598,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-121@11.[212,1376,554,1890]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 7. Superciliaris tawaiensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH), genitalia. A. Penis, lateral view.B. Penis, ventral view. C. Anal tube, dorsal view. D. Anal tube, lateral view. E. Style, lateral view. F. Style, dorsal view. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761698" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761698/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="87">Fig. 7C–D</figureCitation>
). Phallobase vertically elongate, narrow, curved (in lateral view), with median groove ventrally; each dorso-lateral phallobase lobe truncate apically, with short horn-shaped process (
<figureCitation box="[849,980,506,533]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[187,230,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[259,1323,598,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-121@11.[212,1376,554,1890]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 7. Superciliaris tawaiensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH), genitalia. A. Penis, lateral view.B. Penis, ventral view. C. Anal tube, dorsal view. D. Anal tube, lateral view. E. Style, lateral view. F. Style, dorsal view. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761698" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761698/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="87">Fig. 7A–B</figureCitation>
). Ventral phallobase lobe short and wide, widely and deeply concave apically (
<figureCitation box="[709,803,542,568]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[187,230,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[259,1323,598,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-121@11.[212,1376,554,1890]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 7. Superciliaris tawaiensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH), genitalia. A. Penis, lateral view.B. Penis, ventral view. C. Anal tube, dorsal view. D. Anal tube, lateral view. E. Style, lateral view. F. Style, dorsal view. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761698" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761698/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="87">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus with pair of long ventral hooks (
<superScript attach="none" box="[1339,1348,541,555]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="87">4</superScript>
/5 of aedeagus length) arising subapically and with several notches apically. Style with nearly straight hind margin (in lateral view) (
<figureCitation box="[491,583,612,638]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[187,230,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[259,1323,598,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-121@11.[212,1376,554,1890]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 7. Superciliaris tawaiensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH), genitalia. A. Penis, lateral view.B. Penis, ventral view. C. Anal tube, dorsal view. D. Anal tube, lateral view. E. Style, lateral view. F. Style, dorsal view. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761698" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761698/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="87">Fig. 7E</figureCitation>
). Capitulum on distinct neck, with wide lateral tooth, not narrowing apically (in dorsal view) (
